LAFIA – Dr Nicolas Felix, a presidential aspirant on the platform of the ruling All Progressive Congress (APC) on Wednesday promised to fix the economy and tackle the prevalence of insecurity situation bedevilling the country if elected as a president in 2023, general election. Felix made his plan known when while interacting with the youths at the ministry of youths and sports in Lafia, the Nasarawa State capital. He explained that if elected as Nigeria’s president in 2023, the youth would form 80 % of his cabinet. -Advertisement- Felix also disclosed that if elected he would create a level playground for business activities to strive; adding that it’s the business activities that drive economy. “No country grows economically if is not secured. If we can’t fix the security problems we can’t think of fixing the economy. “When I want to travel to my country to contest as a president one foreigners told me not to go that my country is not saved, I told no I’m going, so if you fix security you have fix economy. “We will equip our police officers, we will equip our soldiers, will take care of security men, we will allow them to take a bribe, anybody who takes bribe we will deal with him,” he said. He however called on APC delegates to vote for youth aspirants who would change the fortune of our teeming youths in the country. POLL Responding to the commissioner of youth and sports Lucky Yargwa, who apart from the lauded governor Abdullahi Sule for carrying youth along in his government said he’s going to lobby delegates to vote for Dr Felix, who is a young aspirant to clinch the party ticket in the forthcoming APC Presidential primary.